                                "byte_start": 84358,
                                "byte_stop": 109018,
                                "text": "The opinions of the Court in two cases will be announced by Justice Thomas."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 6.16,
                        "stop": 298.945,
                        "byte_start": 109018,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15100,
                            "name": "Clarence Thomas",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/clarence_thomas",
                            "last_name": "Thomas",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2744,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 688194000,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "George H. W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2744"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32680,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49064,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/clarence_thomas.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8870,
                            "identifier": "clarence_thomas"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 6.16,
                                "stop": 15.521,
                                "byte_start": 109018,
                                "byte_stop": 146529,
                                "text": "First case I have to announce is No. 99-579, Harris Trust \u0026 Savings Bank versus Salomon Smith Barney."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 15.521,
                                "stop": 22.14,
                                "byte_start": 146529,
                                "byte_stop": 172965,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on a writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Seventh Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 22.14,
                                "stop": 47.915,
                                "byte_start": 172965,
                                "byte_stop": 276097,
                                "text": "Section 406 of the Employee Retirement Income Security Act, ERISA, bars a fiduciary of an employee benefit plan from causing the plan to engage in certain prohibited transactions with a party in interest, a term which is defined to encompass entities that a fiduciary might be inclined to favor at the expense of the plan\u2019s beneficiaries."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 47.915,
                                "stop": 69.806,
                                "byte_start": 276097,
                                "byte_stop": 363659,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on the assumption that the Ameritech Pension Trust, an ERISA Plan, entered into a transaction prohibited by Section 406 with respondent Salomon Smith Barney, a non-fiduciary party in interest, whereby Salomon received assets from the plan."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 69.806,
                                "stop": 91.016,
                                "byte_start": 363659,
                                "byte_stop": 448505,
                                "text": "The plan\u0027s fiduciaries, petitioners Harris Trust \u0026 Ameritech Corporation brought suit against Salomon under section 502(a)(3) which authorizes a fiduciary to bring a civil action to obtain appropriate equitable relief to redress violations of ERISA Title I."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 91.016,
                                "stop": 112.962,
                                "byte_start": 448505,
                                "byte_stop": 536276,
                                "text": "Salomon moved for summary judgment, arguing that section 502(a)(3) authorizes suit only against parties upon whom a duty is expressly imposed by one of Title I\u2019s substantive provisions, and asserting that Section 406 does not expressly impose such a duty on a nonfiduciary in interest."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 112.962,
                                "stop": 117.734,
                                "byte_start": 536276,
                                "byte_stop": 555398,
                                "text": "The District Court rejected this argument and denied summary judgment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 117.734,
                                "stop": 121.853,
                                "byte_start": 555398,
                                "byte_stop": 571803,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals for the Seventh Circuit reversed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 121.853,
                                "stop": 130.369,
                                "byte_start": 571803,
                                "byte_stop": 605867,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed with the Clerk today, we reverse the judgment of the Court of Appeals and remand for further proceedings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 130.369,
                                "stop": 157.312,
                                "byte_start": 605867,
                                "byte_stop": 713700,
                                "text": "While we agree with Salomon that Section 406 expressly imposes a duty only on a plan fiduciary, and not on a nonfiduciary party in interest, we reject Salomon\u2019s assumption that a section 502(a)(3) suit is available only against a defendant upon whom a duty is expressly imposed by one of Title I\u2019s substantive provisions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 157.312,
                                "stop": 173.475,
                                "byte_start": 713700,
                                "byte_stop": 778275,
                                "text": "Rather, we hold that section 502(a)(3) itself imposes certain duties; in this case, it imposes a duty on a nonfiduciary party in interest who has received plan assets in violation of Section 406."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 173.475,
                                "stop": 191.391,
                                "byte_start": 778275,
                                "byte_stop": 849955,
                                "text": "This conclusion is supported by the language of Section 502(a)(3) which authorizes a suit for appropriate equitable relief to redress a violation of Title I, but does not specify which parties may be proper defendants."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 191.391,
                                "stop": 215.566,
                                "byte_start": 849955,
                                "byte_stop": 946712,
                                "text": "Another provision of section 502(l) confirms this conclusion in so far as it contemplates a suit by the Secretary of Labor under Section 502(a)(5) against defendants upon whom a duty is not expressly imposed by one of Title I\u2019s substantive provisions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 215.566,
                                "stop": 228.951,
                                "byte_start": 946712,
                                "byte_stop": 1000211,
                                "text": "As we explained in our decision in Martin, Section 502(a)(5) and Section 502(a)(3) must be interpreted similarly in light of their similar language."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 228.951,
                                "stop": 245.255,
                                "byte_start": 1000211,
                                "byte_stop": 1065413,
                                "text": "Although Section 502(a)(3) as noted does not expressly indicate who may be a defendant, it does effectively impose certain limits by virtue of its caveat that the retrospective relief sought the appropriate equitable relief."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 245.255,
                                "stop": 268.965,
                                "byte_start": 1065413,
                                "byte_stop": 1160289,
                                "text": "The common law of trusts informs our understanding of this phrase, that common law, a fiduciary or beneficiary of a trust could bring suit against a transferee for value of planned assets that were obtained in breach of the trust unless the transferee lack actual or constructive knowledge of the circumstances giving rise to the breach."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 268.965,
                                "stop": 279.438,
                                "byte_start": 1160289,
                                "byte_stop": 1202190,
                                "text": "Here, the antecedent breach is a violation of section 406, and Salomon received planned assets by virtue of that transaction."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 279.438,
                                "stop": 290.666,
                                "byte_start": 1202190,
                                "byte_stop": 1247120,
                                "text": "But it remains to be decided on remand whether Salomon possessed actual or constructive knowledge of the circumstances giving rise to the violation of Section 406."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 290.666,
                                "stop": 296.54,
                                "byte_start": 1247120,
                                "byte_stop": 1270526,
                                "text": "Accordingly, we reverse the Seventh Circuit\u2019s judgment and remand for further proceedings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 296.54,
                                "stop": 298.945,
                                "byte_start": 1270526,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
